  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2005-05-05",
    "date": "2005-05-17T14:36:29Z",
    "text": "Fair Taxes for Seniors Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide a one-time increase (from $250,000 to $500,000, or from $500,000 to $1 million for married taxpayers filing joint returns) in the exclusion of gain from the sale of a principal residence by a taxpayer who has attained the age of 50 before such sale. Provides that in the case of a joint return, only one spouse need satisfy the age requirement."
